&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’re an analytical, execution-oriented finance leader with strong business acumen and a passion for GTM strategy. You thrive in fast-moving, ambiguous environments and balance strategic thinking with hands-on work. If you want to help Stripe scale its enterprise footprint and drive decisions through data, we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years in FP&amp;amp;A, Strategic Finance, or GTM Finance supporting enterprise sales teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to analyze pipeline health, forecast revenue, and model user and sales dynamics in complex B2B settings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of partnering with senior GTM leaders and influencing decisions through financial insight.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong financial modeling experience and familiarity with large, multi-variable planning tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in SQL to independently query and manipulate complex datasets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3 years of people management experience with success leading high-performing finance teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and presentation skills; ability to distill complex concepts into clear, actionable insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable operating in fast-paced, ambiguous environments; able to balance strategy with tactical execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working at a high-growth technology or financial services company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Anaplan, Tableau or other equivalent application experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced SQL skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in data visualization and dashboarding&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies use Stripe to accept payments online and in person, embed financial services, power custom revenue models, and build a more profitable business. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Communications team builds and protects Stripe’s reputation and influence across the world. We’re looking for a highly entrepreneurial and creative professional to lead our regional communications as we grow our business across the Asia-Pacific region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is both strategic and hands-on. They’re an exceptional strategist, with a proven ability to synthesize a wide range of inputs and perspectives into an effective game plan. They’re entrepreneurial and pragmatic, enjoying the adrenaline rush of shipping ambitious projects at pace and keen to invent new approaches rather than reverting to the familiar. They have a deep understanding of regional issues and economic trends, and an understanding of how financial infrastructure drives growth. They’re an excellent manager and coach, able to accelerate the development of high-performing colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Define and own our communications strategy for the APAC region,&lt;/strong&gt; including our Singapore headquarters and Southeast Asia and India&lt;strong&gt;,&lt;/strong&gt; building the right approach to support the growth of our users and of Stripe’s business in the region.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Develop and execute creative, high-engagement communications initiatives&lt;/strong&gt;. Use a first-principles approach to build creative campaigns that strengthen our reputation in the region and advance economic growth.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work closely with Stripe users and partners&lt;/strong&gt; to infuse their voices into campaigns, news announcements, and other activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Develop and maintain relationships &lt;/strong&gt;with Stripe users, influencers, reporters, and opinion formers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manage our team of APAC country comms leads&lt;/strong&gt;, including our leads for Australia and New Zealand, Japan, and Greater China.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12+ years of relevant working experience in communications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stellar writing ability.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep knowledge of the APAC region (preferably including experience working across Southeast Asia and/or India).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An excellent people manager and coach.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong corporate communications experience, including issues management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You should include these in your application:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
