&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Stripe, our Mexico City office is a vibrant hub at the forefront of our mission to reshape the financial landscape for businesses worldwide. Our team prioritizes collaboration, innovation, and excellence. As a member of the Mexico City team, you&#39;ll be part of a mission-driven community dedicated to enhancing the global economy and increasing the GDP of the internet. We strive for excellence by creating with craft and beauty, while having fun and celebrating our successes together.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We cultivate a culture of collaboration, inclusivity and support where every team member’s voice matters. Our commitment shines through as we handle over a million support cases each year, empowering our users not just to solve problems but to achieve their goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bridge, a Stripe company, is a rapidly growing business and the number of developers integrating our APIs is growing quickly. We partner with developers to understand their use cases and guide them in integrating with our APIs. We’re a small but mighty team that’s expanding global coverage and is looking to make our first Activation Specialists hires in Mexico City.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you’ll work directly with developers as they integrate with Bridge APIs, guiding them through the onboarding process and helping them go live successfully. You’ll play a key role in resolving early-stage technical challenges, ensuring a smooth activation experience, and accelerating time-to-value for our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Activation Specialist, you’ll collaborate across Product, Solutions Engineering, and Support teams to unblock customers, improve onboarding workflows, and ensure high-quality handoffs. Beyond day-to-day activation support, you’ll contribute to the growth of our onboarding operation- enhancing areas such as workflow optimization, documentation, tooling, metrics, and reporting. This is a high-impact role with visibility across the business, ideal for someone who enjoys solving technical problems, working with developers, and improving processes at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A few key features include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Specialized experts: Activation specialists provide experience helping customers integrate Bridge technology in various use cases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project management consists of a kick off call, regular check-ins, Slack Q&amp;amp;A to help unblock your team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Product workshops and training for Bridge’s dashboard&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively providing technical guidance and support to users during their onboarding journey with Bridge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver pre-built technical workshops and kick off calls to users.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide light touch project management for ongoing Bridge implementations and timely escalate any delays with planned go-live dates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshooting technical issues and providing timely solutions to ensure a smooth onboarding process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with cross-functional teams to address user queries and concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining accurate records of user interactions, issues, and resolutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Anticipating and addressing potential technical challenges during the onboarding process. Proactively propose improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Offering guidance on best practices, product features, and account setup to ensure user success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously updating knowledge of Bridge’s products, features, and updates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Escalating complex technical issues to appropriate teams for resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing exceptional customer service to ensure a positive onboarding experience for users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributing to the improvement of onboarding processes and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for dynamic and curious people that have a passion for solving global user issues, building operations, driving process improvements and want to play a front-line role in building this new operational capability for Bridge and accelerating Bridge’s growth. If you like challenging, scaled problems and are an amazing teammate, we want to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Onboarding Specialist is responsible for providing technical guidance to users during their onboarding journey with Bridge. They proactively address technical queries, troubleshoot issues, and provide solutions to ensure a seamless onboarding process. They work closely with users to understand their needs, offer guidance on best practices, and anticipate and address any potential technical challenges. The Onboarding Specialist collaborates with cross-functional teams, escalates issues as needed, and maintains accurate records of user interactions. Their goal is to provide exceptional customer service and ensure that users have a positive and successful onboarding experience with Bridge.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
